args: Welcome, one and all, as we celebrate\nyet another iteration of our beloved\nfestival of floating lanterns!
Easy, Grandma. Stay loose now, or you'll\nwear yourself out before things go down.
Thank you, Douleur. But if you ＂Grandma＂\nme again, I'm tossing you in the drink.
Just a moment, dear.\nI'm getting one ready for you.
They place paper lanterns on little\nboats and float them down the river.\nWhat a curious festival.
It's supposed to be a ritual for laying\nthe spirits of our ancestors to rest.
Oh, it's you. Thank you for\nthe handkerchief earlier.
I got your message, by the way.\nLeave it to me.
(She wasn't the one who wrote it?)
Do you mind if I join you? I've got some\ntime to kill while I wait for someone.
Not at all. And by ＂someone,＂ do you mean\nthat little sister of yours I spied you with\nearlier?
I usually go with my sister, but this year,\nI'm actually hoping to spend it with a\nchildhood friend.
Ah, so that's why you two were arguing.\nHe must be someone special.
He's special to me, anyway.\nI couldn't tell you how he feels about me.\nEspecially considering that he's LATE.
Do you have someone like that, ma'am?
I did, once. We were to visit a festival\ntogether, but I let my chance slip away.
Because of the rains, you mean? I heard\nthe royals couldn't come because of that.
Someone from the royal family was meant\nto come here?
That's right. Our lantern festival is based\non an old Hinomotoan tradition, so they\nwanted to come see it for themselves.
One of the villages I'm set to look in on is\nholding an event in Hinomotoan fashion.\nWould you accompany me on my visit?
＂It would have been a tragedy no matter\nwhere it happened, but when I heard the\nvillage's name, I stopped short. It was—＂
He and I were to come here.\nI was to wear this yukata.
Huh? What's that rumbling?\nIt's coming from upriver.
Aaah! The river! It's a flood!
We've got to get out of here,\nNOW! Or we're all dead!

＂Laws of the deep, thy mistress
commands: let mana's flow form
a dam to stem the raging tide.＂
—Barrier wall, activate!
(It's no use! The water's coming too fast!\nIt's going to break through!)
The water's receding.\nAre... Are we saved?
Not gonna lie, I gave up hope there for\na hot minute, but you came in clutch.\nAdrenaline's a helluva drug, I guess!
How strange. I felt powerful mana surge\nthrough me. But where did it come from?
Aw, worry about that later.\nYou just saved a whole village, woman!
Which means their grudge goes out the\nwindow and we get to BOOK it back to the\nland of the liv—
I won't let you. Not until every last iota\nof the pain I felt wracks your feeble body.
I've been through this over and over,\nwaiting to hear his answer.
Over...and over and over and over and over\nand over and over and over and over and\novernadoverandoverandoverandoverand
Uhhhh... I'm gettin' some reeeal\npsycho vibes from this one, Cass.
You think some water hurt that day? ...Hee.\nHee ha ha... Ah ha ha ha ha... aH ha hA Ha\nAhh Ha hA HA ha ah HA AH HA HA HA hA
Ngh?! This suffocating aura!\nSo evil. Is she—
Offer their lives as tribute to me, my\npeople. Let them suffer as we have!
Okay, I'm all for a sensible costume\nchange, but this is getting very NOT OKAY.
All right, spill. What's WITH that chick?!
A soul stained black by grief—a ghast.\nI was wrong about what's happening here.
This place isn't a manifestation of the\nvillagers' collective memories. It's the\nwork of a single ghast.
Then what are the rest of them?
Poor souls trapped in the prison of her\nmemories, condemned to play their parts\nin the recurring drama of her final hours.
Unless her grudge is dispelled, they can\nnever return to where they belong.
What's the deal with ol' ghasty-gal, then?\nI thought she was all aggrieved from dying\nin the flood 40 years ago.
No. Her real grief lies in—
Rgh, she's already caught up!\nWhat's the plan, Gran?!
This is my special place.\nIt's a secret to everybody but me.
You don't say? Well, hopefully\nthat buys us a little time, then.
Also, side note: Who the heck are you?\nWhy are you helping us?
When you led me by the hand, I couldn't\nhelp but notice yours was tiny and smooth.\n＂Moisturized,＂ even.
The puzzle pieces are finally clicking into\nplace. You were the one who put the note\nin that handkerchief.
I have questions, little one.\nAbout your big sister.
